        public void flush(GatheringByteChannel file,
         boolean clear)
           throws IOException
        Flushes the sorted contents to the given file.
        Parameters:
        file - typically a FileChannel
        clear - if true, then the clear() is called on return. The reason why the parameter is offered is it's marginally more efficient to pass true than to pass false and followed by clear().
        Throws:
        IOException
